'''Kataoka Shrine''' (かたおかじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} in Honmachi 2-chōme, {{jalink|Ōji|Q1346392}}, {{jalink|Kitakatsuragi District|Q1131013}}, {{jalink|Nara Prefecture|Q131287}}. It is a {{jalink|Shikinaisha}} ({{jalink|myōjin taisha|Q9610964}}), and its former rank was {{jalink|Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines#Shosha|Q712534|gōsha}}.

=== History ===
=== Outline ===
It is said that in ancient times it stood at the locale of Ōmine in Honmachi, {{jalink|Ōji|Q1346392}}. In {{jalink|Daidō (Japan)|Q1373191|Daidō}} 1 ({{jalink|806|Q30021}}), it was allotted {{jalink|shinpū|Q1689534}} of 7 households in Yamato, 8 in Tōtōmi, and 25 in Ōmi ({{jalink|Shinshō Kakuchokufu-shō|Q11502312}}), and in the {{jalink|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932}} it was ranked as a {{jalink|myōjin taisha|Q9610964}}, a noted shrine included in rain-prayer rites.

In {{jalink|Meiji|Q3125096}} 6 ({{jalink|1873|Q7757}}), in April, it was ranked as {{jalink|gōsha|Q134917316}}.

=== Divine rank ===
*{{jalink|Ten'an (Japan)|Q1075611|Ten'an}} 3 ({{jalink|859|Q23897}}), {{jalink|January 27|Q2284}}: promoted from Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade, Merit Rank 8 to Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade, Merit Rank 8 (''{{jalink|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981}}'')

=== Access ===
* 15 minutes on foot from {{jalink|Ōji Station|Q856582}} on the {{jalink|Yamatoji Line|Q1151659}} and {{jalink|Wakayama Line|Q511543}} of {{jalink|JR West|Q502125}}

