'''Kataoka Shrine''' (かたおかじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} in Honmachi 2-chōme, {{ill|lt=Ōji|Q1346392|WD=Q1346392}}, {{ill|lt=Kitakatsuragi District|Q1131013|WD=Q1131013}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=UNKNOWN|WD=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=myōjin taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964}}), and its former rank was {{ill|lt=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines#Shosha|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=gōsha}}.

=== History ===
=== Outline ===
It is said that in ancient times it stood at the locale of Ōmine in Honmachi, {{ill|lt=Ōji|Q1346392|WD=Q1346392}}. In {{ill|lt=Daidō (Japan)|Q1373191|WD=Q1373191|lt=Daidō}} 1 ({{ill|lt=806|Q30021|WD=Q30021}}), it was allotted {{ill|lt=shinpū|Q1689534|WD=Q1689534}} of 7 households in Yamato, 8 in Tōtōmi, and 25 in Ōmi ({{ill|lt=Shinshō Kakuchokufu-shō|Q11502312|WD=Q11502312}}), and in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932}} it was ranked as a {{ill|lt=myōjin taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964}}, a noted shrine included in rain-prayer rites.

In {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096}} 6 ({{ill|lt=1873|Q7757|WD=Q7757}}), in April, it was ranked as {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316}}.

=== Divine rank ===
*{{ill|lt=Ten'an (Japan)|Q1075611|WD=Q1075611|lt=Ten'an}} 3 ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|WD=Q23897}}), {{ill|lt=January 27|Q2284|WD=Q2284}}: promoted from Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade, Merit Rank 8 to Senior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade, Merit Rank 8 (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|WD=Q1052981}}'')

=== Access ===
* 15 minutes on foot from {{ill|lt=Ōji Station|Q856582|WD=Q856582}} on the {{ill|lt=Yamatoji Line|Q1151659|WD=Q1151659}} and {{ill|lt=Wakayama Line|Q511543|WD=Q511543}} of {{ill|lt=JR West|Q502125|WD=Q502125}}

